cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.DS 

This paper deals with a machine learning problem of binary classification, specifically in the context of positive-unlabeled (PU) learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the incorporation of biased negative (bN) data, which could fall under sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CV (Computer Vision) depending on the application domain. The use of empirical risk minimization and example-reweighting algorithms suggests a focus on optimization and algorithms, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
